name: Jamie Smith
interests: Sculpting, hiking, cooking, volunteering at local animal shelter
summary:
Jamie Smith is a non-binary, 32-year-old graphic designer based in Los Angeles, California. They are of Hispanic/Latino ethnicity and are fluent in English, Spanish, and American Sign Language. Jamie holds a graduate degree from the University of California and carries a passion for charitable work, environmentalism, and equal rights. They are looking for a life partner while preferring monogamy.

In their leisure time, Jamie enjoys sculpting, hiking, and cooking. They also volunteer at a local animal shelter. Jamie identifies as spiritual, maintains liberal political views, and has a love for pets, having a cat and a dog. They are non-drinkers and non-smokers with an active lifestyle. Jamie does not have children but has expressed a desire to have them in the future. 

Their potential partner preferences include someone aged between 30-40, who also enjoys an active lifestyle, is a non-smoker, and non-drinker with no kids. However, this ideal partner should also want children in the future.
